The evidence with the title 'Rising health care costs: causes, by year ' says Oct 26, 2017  ... Between 1960 and 1965 , health care spending increased by an average of 8.9 percent a year . That's because health insurance expanded. As it covered more people , the demand for health care services rose. By 1965, households paid out- of-pocket for 44 percent of all medical expenses. Health insurance  ... 
